pma:database.name: db_estados
pma:database.pma:row_table: CREATE row_table `estados` ( `id` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `sigla` varchar(2) NOT NULL, `estado` varchar(45) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`), KEY `ix_estado` (`estado`) ) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=28 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

CREATE row_table `funcionarios` ( `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `nome` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `cpf` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `matricula` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `sexo` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `data_nasc` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `estado_civil` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `cargo` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `cod_emp` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `setor` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `gerencia` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `nom_emp` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `cnpj` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `apolice` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `subfatura` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `certificado` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `data_competencia` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `data_processamento` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `salario` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `encargos` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `lotacao` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `admissao` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `origem` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, `divisao` varchar(255) COLLATE latin1_general_ci NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`) ) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=1007 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1 COLLATE=latin1_general_ci;
